Name: Section
Account: 4. Projected Income: The Estimated Annual Income and Estimated Remaining Income in the Projected Income report assume dividend and bond payments remain constant throughout the year. These positions and interest rates are based on the previous business day.

Name: Section
Account: 5. Risk Measures: Historical US 3 Month Treasury Bill rates are used as the risk free rates when calculating Alpha, the Sharpe ratio, the Sortino ratio, and the downside deviation.
